{{This date in recent years}}
{{Day}}

==Events==
* [[755]] &ndash; [[An Lushan]] revolts against [[Chancellor of the Tang Dynasty|Chancellor]] [[Yang Guozhong]] at [[Yanjing]], initiating the [[An Lushan Rebellion]] during the [[Tang Dynasty]] of [[China]].
*[[1431]] &ndash; [[Henry VI of England]] is crowned [[List of French monarchs|King of France]] at [[Notre Dame de Paris|Notre Dame]] in [[Paris]], [[France]].
*[[1497]] &ndash; [[Vasco da Gama]] rounds the [[Cape of Good Hope]], the point where [[Bartolomeu Dias]] had previously turned back to [[Portugal]].
*[[1575]] &ndash; The [[1575 Valdivia earthquake]] takes place.
*[[1598]] &ndash; [[Japanese invasions of Korea (1592–1598)|Seven Year War]]: [[Battle of Noryang]] &ndash; Chinese General [[Chen Lin]] heavily damage the Japanese fleet, however, the Japanese army succeeds in retreating.
*[[1653]] &ndash; [[Interregnum (England)|English Interregnum]]: [[The Protectorate]] &ndash; [[Oliver Cromwell]] becomes [[Lord Protector]] of the [[Commonwealth of England]], [[Scotland]] and [[Ireland]].
*[[1689]] &ndash; [[Convention Parliament (1689)|Convention Parliament]]: The ''Declaration of Right'' is embodied in the ''[[Bill of Rights 1689|Bill of Rights]]''.
*[[1707]] &ndash; [[Hōei eruption of Mount Fuji|Last recorded eruption]] of [[Mount Fuji]] in Japan.
*[[1761]] &ndash; [[Seven Years' War]]: After a [[Siege of Kolberg (Seven Years' War)|four-month siege]], the [[Russia]]ns under [[Pyotr Rumyantsev]] take the [[Prussia]]n fortress of [[Kołobrzeg]].
*[[1773]] &ndash; [[American Revolution]]: [[Boston Tea Party]] &ndash; Members of the [[Sons of Liberty]] disguised as [[Mohawk people|Mohawk Indians]] dump hundreds of crates of tea into [[Boston]] harbor as a protest against the [[Tea Act]].
*[[1811]] &ndash; [[1811–1812 New Madrid earthquakes|The first two in a series]] of four severe [[earthquake]]s occur in the vicinity of [[New Madrid Seismic Zone|New Madrid, Missouri]]. These four so-called mega-quakes are believed to be an ongoing cataclysmic danger that could reprise the 1811-12 series of 2,000 quakes that affected the lands of what would be eight of today's [[Heartland (United States)|heartland]] states of the United States.
*[[1826]] &ndash; [[Benjamin W. Edwards]] rides into Mexican controlled [[Nacogdoches, Texas]] and declares himself ruler of the [[Fredonian Rebellion|Republic of Fredonia]].
*[[1838]] &ndash; [[Battle of Blood River]]: [[Voortrekkers]] led by [[Andries Pretorius]] and [[Sarel Cilliers]] defeat [[Zulu people|Zulu]] [[impi]]s, led by Dambuza (Nzobo) and [[Ndlela kaSompisi]] in what is today [[KwaZulu-Natal]], [[South Africa]].
*[[1850]] &ndash; [[History of New Zealand]]: The ''[[Charlotte Jane]]'' and the ''[[Randolph (ship)|Randolph]]'' bring the first of the [[Canterbury Association|Canterbury Pilgrims]] to [[Lyttelton, New Zealand]].
*[[1863]] &ndash; [[American Civil War]]: [[Joseph E. Johnston]] replaces [[Braxton Bragg]] as commander of the [[Army of Tennessee]].
*[[1864]] &ndash; American Civil War: [[Franklin–Nashville Campaign]] &ndash; [[Battle of Nashville]] &ndash; Major General [[George Henry Thomas|George Thomas]]'s [[Union (American Civil War)|Union]] forces defeat Lieutenant General [[John Bell Hood]]'s [[Army of Tennessee|Confederate Army of Tennessee]].
*[[1903]] &ndash; [[The Taj Mahal Palace Hotel|Taj Mahal Palace & Tower]] first opened its doors to the guests.
*[[1907]] &ndash; The [[Great White Fleet]] begins its circumnavigation of the world.
*[[1912]] &ndash; [[First Balkan War]]: The [[Battle of Elli]] takes place.
*[[1914]] &ndash; [[World War I]]: German battleships under [[Franz von Hipper]] bombard the English ports of [[Hartlepool]] and [[Scarborough, North Yorkshire|Scarborough]].
*[[1918]] &ndash; [[Vincas Mickevičius-Kapsukas]] declares the formation of the [[Lithuanian Soviet Socialist Republic (1918–1919)|Lithuanian Soviet Socialist Republic]].
*[[1920]] &ndash; The [[1920 Haiyuan earthquake|Haiyuan earthquake]], magnitude 8.5, rocks the [[Gansu]] province in China, killing an estimated 200,000.
*[[1922]] &ndash; [[President of Poland]] [[Gabriel Narutowicz]] is assassinated by [[Eligiusz Niewiadomski]] at the Zachęta Gallery in [[Warsaw]].
*[[1930]] &ndash; Bank robber [[Herman Lamm]] and members of his crew are killed by a 200-strong posse, following a botched bank robbery in [[Clinton, Indiana]].
*[[1937]] &ndash; [[Theodore Cole and Ralph Roe]] attempt to escape from the [[United States|American]] federal prison on [[Alcatraz Island]] in [[San Francisco Bay]]; neither is ever seen again.
*[[1938]] &ndash; [[Adolf Hitler]] institutes the [[Cross of Honor of the German Mother]].
*[[1941]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: Japanese forces occupy [[Miri]], [[Sarawak]].
*[[1942]] &ndash; [[The Holocaust|Holocaust]]: [[Heinrich Himmler]] orders that [[Romani people|Roma]] candidates for extermination be deported to [[Auschwitz concentration camp|Auschwitz]].
*[[1944]] &ndash; World War II: The [[Battle of the Bulge]] begins with the surprise offensive of three [[German Army (1935–1945)|German armies]] through the [[Ardennes]] forest.
*[[1946]] &ndash; [[Thailand]] joins the [[United Nations]].
*[[1947]] &ndash; [[William Shockley]], [[John Bardeen]] and [[Walter Houser Brattain|Walter Brattain]] build the first practical [[point-contact transistor]].
*[[1950]] &ndash; [[Korean War]]: [[President of the United States|U.S. President]] [[Harry S. Truman]] declares a state of emergency, after Chinese troops enter the fight with [[Communism|communist]] [[North Korea]].
*[[1957]] &ndash; Sir [[Feroz Khan Noon]] replaces [[Ibrahim Ismail Chundrigar]] as [[Prime Minister of Pakistan]].
*[[1960]] &ndash; [[1960 New York mid-air collision|1960 New York air disaster]]: While approaching [[New York City|New York, New York]]'s [[John F. Kennedy International Airport|Idlewild Airport]], a [[United Airlines]] [[Douglas DC-8]] collides with a [[Trans World Airlines|TWA]] [[Lockheed L-1049 Super Constellation|Lockheed Super Constellation]] in a blinding [[Winter storm|snowstorm]] over [[Staten Island]], killing 134.
*[[1965]] &ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: General [[William Westmoreland]] sends [[United States Secretary of Defense|U.S. Secretary of Defense]] [[Robert McNamara]] a request for 243,000 more men by the end of [[1966]].
*[[1968]] &ndash; [[Second Vatican Council]]: Official revocation of the [[Alhambra Decree|Edict of Expulsion of Jews from Spain]].
*[[1971]] &ndash; [[Bangladesh Liberation War]] and [[Indo-Pakistani War of 1971]]: The surrender of the [[Pakistan Army]] brings an end to both conflicts.
*  1971   &ndash; "National Day" of the Kingdom of [[Bahrain]] is celebrated. Not to be confused with [[Bahrain Independence Day]] which took place on August 15, 1971.
*[[1972]] &ndash; Vietnam War: [[Henry Kissinger]] announces that [[North Vietnam]] has left private peace negotiations, in Paris, France.
*[[1972]] &ndash; [[Vijay Diwas (India)|Vijay Diwas]]:  (Victory Day) is commemorated every 16 December in [[India]] as it marks its military victory over Pakistan in 1971 during the [[Indo-Pakistani War of 1971]].
*[[1978]] &ndash; [[Cleveland]], [[Ohio]] becomes the first post-[[Great Depression|Depression]] era city to default on its loans, owing $14,000,000 to local banks.
*[[1979]] &ndash; [[Libya]] joins four other [[OPEC]] nations in raising crude oil prices, having an immediate dramatic effect on the United States.
*[[1985]] &ndash; [[Sicilian Mafia|Mafia]]: In New York City, New York, [[Paul Castellano]] and [[Thomas Bilotti]] are shot dead on the orders of [[John Gotti]], who assumes leadership of the [[Gambino family]].
*[[1986]] &ndash; Revolt in [[Kazakhstan]] against [[Communist Party of Kazakhstan]], known as [[Jeltoqsan]], which becomes the first sign of ethnic strife during [[President of the Soviet Union|Soviet President]] [[Mikhail Gorbachev]]'s tenure
*[[1989]] &ndash; Protests break out in [[Timișoara]], [[Romania]] in response to an attempt by the government to evict dissident [[Hungary|Hungarian]] pastor [[László Tőkés]].
*  1989   &ndash; Walter LeRoy Moody begins his [[Terrorism|terrorist]] bombing streak when he sends Judge [[Robert Smith Vance]] a bomb in the mail, instantly killing him near his house in [[Birmingham, Alabama]].
*[[1991]] &ndash; Kazakhstan gains its independence from the Soviet Union.
*[[1997]] &ndash; An episode of ''[[Pokémon (anime)|Pokémon]]'', "[[Dennō Senshi Porygon]]", aired in Japan induces seizures in 685 Japanese children.
*[[1998]] &ndash; [[Iraq disarmament crisis]]: [[Bombing of Iraq (December 1998)|Operation Desert Fox]] &ndash; The United States and [[United Kingdom]] bomb targets in [[Iraq]].
*[[2003]] &ndash; [[President of the United States|President]] [[George W. Bush]] signs the [[CAN-SPAM Act of 2003]] into law. The law establishes the United States' first national standards for the sending of commercial e-mail and requires the [[Federal Trade Commission]] to enforce its provisions.
*[[2009]] &ndash; [[Avatar (2009 film)]] is released internationally. It would later be the first film to gross $2 billion and the [[highest grossing movie]] of all time.
*[[2012]] &ndash; [[2012 Delhi gang rape|A brutal gang rape]] in [[Delhi]] sparks widespread demonstrations across [[India]].

